I'll handle the timeout by retrying the data_processing_parser tool with a shorter timeout setting to prevent the same issue.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {
    "timeout": 30
  }
}</tool_call>

Now that we have successfully parsed the input data, I'll proceed with the next step in the workflow which is data validation using the data_processing_validator tool.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {
        "type": "array"
      }
    },
    "required": ["data"]
  },
  "data": "data/input.json"
}</tool_call>

            With the data successfully validated, I'll now proceed to transform the data using the data_processing_transformer tool to prepare it for the final filtering step.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {
    "source": "data/input.json",
    "destination": "data/transformed.json"
  }
}</tool_call>

I'll retry the data transformation with a longer timeout setting to ensure completion. This time I'll also specify the input data directly from the previous successful operations.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {
    "timeout": 30,
    "source": "data/input.json",
    "destination": "data/transformed.json"
  }
}</tool_call>

            Now that the data has been successfully transformed, I'll proceed with the final step of filtering the data using the data_processing_filter tool.

<tool_call>data_processing_filter
{
  "source": "data/transformed.json",
  "destination": "data/output.json",
  "filter_criteria": {
    "type": "basic",
    "conditions": []
  }
}</tool_call>
